# Agent Skills (Claude Agent SDK)

Official reference: [Agent Skills in the SDK](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/skills.md).

## How Skills load

- Skills are filesystem artifacts: each skill is a directory with `SKILL.md` (YAML frontmatter + body). Project skills live under `.claude/skills/`; user-wide skills under `~/.claude/skills/`. Plugins can bundle skills too.
- **Default SDK behavior does not load filesystem settings.** To discover Skills, set `setting_sources` (Python) / `settingSources` (TS), e.g. `["user", "project"]`. Include `"project"` if you want repo `.claude/skills/` and project settings; include `"user"` for personal skills.
- **`cwd` matters:** Skills resolve relative to the configured working directory. Point `cwd` at the project root that contains `.claude/skills/` when you want those project skills.

## Enabling the Skill tool

- Add **`"Skill"`** to **`allowed_tools`**. Without it, the model cannot invoke Skills even if they are discovered.
- Other tools (Read, Bash, etc.) are still governed by the same `allowed_tools` / `disallowed_tools` / permission hooks as the rest of the session.

## SDK vs CLI — `allowed-tools` in SKILL.md

- The **`allowed-tools` frontmatter field in `SKILL.md` applies to Claude Code CLI usage, not when using Skills through the SDK. **In SDK apps, control tools only via the main `ClaudeAgentOptions`** (`allowed_tools`, `disallowed_tools`, `can_use_tool`, etc.).

## Troubleshooting (quick)

| Symptom | Check |
|--------|--------|
| No Skills found | `setting_sources` includes the sources you need; `cwd` points at the tree that contains `.claude/skills/`. |
| Skill never runs | `"Skill"` is in `allowed_tools`; improve the Skill `description` in frontmatter so it matches user tasks. |
| Wrong tools inside a Skill | Not fixable via SKILL.md `allowed-tools` in SDK — adjust `allowed_tools` / `disallowed_tools` on `ClaudeAgentOptions`. |

## This repo

- `bot/claude_client.py` builds `ClaudeAgentOptions` (e.g. `cwd`, `disallowed_tools`). To use Skills in production, add `setting_sources` and ensure `"Skill"` is allowed (and not blocked by policy), consistent with the doc above.
